	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: Selling a PowerPak?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The color restrictions on the NES make it hard to make the UI look good, although there's some obvious improvements over the default PowerPak firmware.<br />The most important thing is paying attention to the 90% safe area, which AIUI the current firmware doesn't.<br /><br />There's a bit the FPGA can do to help (like automagic <s>non</s>proportional font support) but you're still kinda hamstrung by the very small source palette, the even smaller active palette, and the 256px width of the screen.<br />The FPGA can also shrink the attribute area from 16×16 to 8×1, which would only help with putting shorter-than-8-pixel text on the screen, because each row of text could draw from a different attribute.<br />Finding a good antialiased font at any smaller size might be difficult, however. (For non-antialised fonts, I suppose the Chicago typeface, or one of the 4x6 tiny fonts, maybe.)

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


